headline: 3 Magnificent S&P 500 Dividend Stocks Down 15% to 65% to Buy and Hold Forever
summary: Alphabet is the cheapest Magnificent Seven stock and is vastly underrated.  Semiconductor equipment supplier Applied Materials should deliver AI-powered double-digit dividend growth.  The beaten-down retailer Target pays almost 5% and has been around since 1902.

headline: Target Delivers 54th Consecutive Annual Dividend Hike
summary: Target Corporation (NYSE:TGT) is one of the best stocks for a retirement stock portfolio.
